// Unit 24 — 후회와 가정
// Regret & Hypotheticals

export default {n:24,lang:"ko",srcLang:"en",track:"v2",title:"후회와 가정",sub:"Regret & Hypotheticals",icon:"😔",level:"B2.1",color:"#9B7EDE",lessons:[
  {id:"kou24l1",title:"아쉬움",icon:"💭",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"The Feeling of Regret",desc:"아쉬움\n→ Korean has rich vocabulary for regret,\nmissed chances, and what could have been.\n\nThis unit teaches you to express:\n- I should have...\n- I almost...\n- If only I had...",goals:["Learn regret and hypothetical vocabulary","Understand Korean emotional concepts of 아쉬움 and 한","Express regret in multiple registers"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"후회",src:"regret",pos:"noun",gender:null,phonetic:"hu-hoe",note:"COMPOUND: 후(after/後) + 회(turn back/悔).\nAfter-turn back: wishing you could go back.\n후회하다 = to regret.",example:"후회해도 소용없어요.\n(Regretting is no use.)",exampleSrc:"Regretting is no use.",funFact:"Korean builds words by combining meaning blocks. Understanding the parts unlocks entire word families."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"아쉽다",src:"regrettable / what a shame",pos:"adj",gender:null,phonetic:"a-swip-da",note:"A uniquely Korean emotion.\nNot just 'sad' but 'wishing things were different.'\n아쉬움 (noun) = the feeling of regret/longing.\nMore about missed potential than actual sadness.",example:"A: 이번 여행 어땠어요? B: 좋았는데 시간이 부족해서 아쉬웠어요. A: 어디를 못 가셨어요? B: 부산 해운대를 못 갔어요. 정말 아쉬워요. A: 거기 일몰이 유명하잖아요. B: 맞아요. 그래서 더 아쉬운 거예요. A: 다음에 꼭 가 보세요. B: 네, 다음에는 시간을 더 내야겠어요. A: 저도 같이 가고 싶어요. B: 좋아요. 같이 계획을 세워요.",exampleSrc:"A: How was your trip? B: It was good but I felt it was a shame there wasn't enough time. A: Where couldn't you go? B: I couldn't go to Haeundae in Busan. I really feel regretful. A: The sunset there is famous, right? B: Exactly. That's why it's even more of a shame. A: Make sure to go next time. B: Yes, I should make more time next time. A: I want to go together too. B: Sure. Let's plan it together.",funFact:"Korean adjectives conjugate like verbs. They change form for tense, politeness, and sentence position."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"그리워하다",src:"to miss (someone/something)",pos:"verb",gender:null,phonetic:"geu-ri-wo-ha-da",note:"From 그립다 (to be missed).\n그리움 = nostalgia, longing.\nDifferent from 보고 싶다 (want to see).",example:"A: 고향 생각 많이 나요? B: 네, 특히 가을이면 고향이 그리워요. A: 어떤 게 제일 그리워요? B: 엄마가 만들어 주신 음식이요. A: 저도 엄마 음식이 그리워요. B: 명절 때 특히 그리움이 커져요. A: 그러면 올해 추석에 고향에 가세요. B: 올해는 꼭 가려고요. 너무 오래 못 갔거든요. A: 가족들이 반가워하시겠어요. B: 네, 벌써부터 설레요.",exampleSrc:"A: Do you think about your hometown a lot? B: Yes, especially in autumn I miss my hometown. A: What do you miss the most? B: The food my mom used to make. A: I miss my mom's food too. B: The longing gets stronger especially during holidays. A: Then go to your hometown this Chuseok. B: I'm definitely planning to this year. I haven't been able to go for too long. A: Your family will be so happy to see you. B: Yes, I'm already excited.",funFact:"Korean verbs always come at the end of the sentence. The ending changes for politeness, tense, and mood."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"돌이키다",src:"to turn back / reverse",pos:"verb",gender:null,phonetic:"do-ri-ki-da",note:"돌이키다 = reverse, undo.\n돌이킬 수 없는 실수 = an irreversible mistake.\nOften used with 시간 (time) or 결정 (decision).",example:"A: 그때 왜 그런 선택을 했을까요? B: 모르겠어요. 돌이키고 싶어요. A: 시간을 돌이킬 수 없잖아요. B: 알아요. 하지만 결정을 바꾸고 싶어요. A: 후회해도 소용없어요. B: 그래도 돌이킬 수 없는 실수라서 마음이 아파요. A: 앞으로 더 신중하게 생각하세요. B: 네, 다시는 같은 실수 안 할게요. A: 그게 제일 중요해요. 과거보다 미래를 보세요. B: 맞아요. 감사합니다.",exampleSrc:"A: Why did you make that choice back then? B: I don't know. I want to take it back. A: You can't turn back time, you know. B: I know. But I want to change my decision. A: Regretting is no use. B: Still, it hurts because it's an irreversible mistake. A: Think more carefully from now on. B: Yes, I won't make the same mistake again. A: That's what matters most. Look at the future, not the past. B: You're right. Thank you.",funFact:"Korean verbs always come at the end of the sentence. The ending changes for politeness, tense, and mood."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"불안",src:"anxiety / unease",pos:"noun",gender:null,phonetic:"bul-an",note:"COMPOUND: 불(not/不) + 안(peace/安).\nNot-peace: inner turmoil.\n불안하다 = to be anxious/uneasy.\n불안감 = sense of anxiety.",example:"미래에 대한 불안이 커요.\n(Anxiety about the future is big.)",exampleSrc:"Anxiety about the future is big.",funFact:"Korean builds words by combining meaning blocks. Understanding the parts unlocks entire word families."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"실수",src:"mistake",pos:"noun",gender:null,phonetic:"sil-su",note:"COMPOUND: 실(lose/失) + 수(hand/手).\nLose-hand: a slip of the hand.\n실수하다 = to make a mistake.\nAlso: 실수로 = by mistake (accidentally).",example:"큰 실수를 했어요.\n(I made a big mistake.)",exampleSrc:"I made a big mistake.",funFact:"Korean builds words by combining meaning blocks. Understanding the parts unlocks entire word families."},
        {type:"tip",title:"아쉬움 vs 후회",deepDive:"The concept of 한 (恨):\n\nDeeper than 후회. A collective Korean emotion:\n- Unresolved grief from historical suffering\n- Personal longing for what was taken away\n- Bittersweet acceptance of life's unfairness\n\n한이 맺히다 = to have 한 build up\n한을 풀다 = to resolve/release 한\n\nThis concept appears in Korean art, music (판소리),\nand literature. Understanding 한 helps you\nunderstand Korean emotional expression.",text:"Korean distinguishes two types of regret:\n\n아쉬움: wishing things COULD HAVE been better\n 아쉽지만 어쩔 수 없어요.\n (It's a shame but can't be helped.)\n Gentle, accepting, bittersweet.\n\n후회: regretting what you DID or DIDN'T do\n 공부 안 한 것을 후회해요.\n (I regret not studying.)\n Stronger, self-blaming.\n\n아쉬움 is about circumstances.\n후회 is about your own choices."},
        {type:"mc",q:"시간을 돌이킬 수 없어요.\nWhat does 돌이키다 mean?",opts:["To turn back / reverse","To regret","To miss","To worry about"],ans:"To turn back / reverse",hint:"돌이키다 = undo, reverse. Can't turn back time."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"After-turn-back emotion. Reverse action.",s:"{1}해도 소용없어요. 시간을 {2} 수 없으니까요.\n(Regretting is no use. Because you can't turn back time.)",blanks:{"1":"후회","2":"돌이킬"},pool:["후회","돌이킬","실수","그리워할","불안","아쉬울"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"아쉽지만 어쩔 수 없어요.\nThe feeling expressed is:",opts:["Bittersweet acceptance (아쉬움)","Strong self-blame (후회)","Anxiety (불안)","Nostalgia (그리움)"],ans:"Bittersweet acceptance (아쉬움)",hint:"아쉽다 = a shame but accepting. Gentler than 후회."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[{trg:"후회",src:"regret"},{trg:"아쉬움",src:"bittersweet longing"},{trg:"불안",src:"anxiety"},{trg:"실수",src:"mistake"}]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["그리워","아쉬워","후회해","불안해"],hint:"Longing for a place. Missing.",s:"고향이 {1}요. 돌아가고 싶어요.\n(I miss my hometown. I want to go back.)",a:"그리워"},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Lose-hand. After-turn-back. Reverse.",s:"큰 {1}를 해서 {2}하고 있어요. 시간을 {3} 수 있다면 좋겠어요.\n(I made a big mistake so I'm regretting it. I wish I could turn back time.)",blanks:{"1":"실수","2":"후회","3":"돌이킬"},pool:["실수","후회","돌이킬","아쉬움","불안","그리워할"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"한 (恨) is best described as:",opts:["Deep unresolved longing and bittersweet acceptance","Simple sadness","Anger at others","Fear of the future"],ans:"Deep unresolved longing and bittersweet acceptance",hint:"한 is a uniquely Korean collective emotional concept."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Not-peace. Written 'and'. After-turn-back.",s:"미래에 대한 {1}이 크{2} {3}도 많아요.\n(Anxiety about the future is big, and regrets are also many.)",blanks:{"1":"불안","2":"며","3":"후회"},pool:["불안","며","후회","실수","고","아쉬움"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Should-have (future modifier + 걸). Adjective polite.",s:"그때 더 열심히 공부{1} 걸. 정말 아쉬{2}요.\n(I should have studied harder then. I really feel regretful.)",blanks:{"1":"할","2":"워"},pool:["할","워","한","어","하","운","를","는"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"아쉽다 vs 후회하다:\n시험을 잘 못 봐서 아쉬워요.\n공부 안 한 것을 후회해요.\nKey difference?\n(Comparing two regret words.)",opts:["아쉽다 = mild disappointment; 후회하다 = active self-blame","Same meaning","아쉽다 = stronger","후회하다 = milder"],ans:"아쉽다 = mild disappointment; 후회하다 = active self-blame",hint:"아쉽다 is softer. 후회 implies you blame yourself."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Polite. Object + cannot.",s:"고향{1} 그리워해{2}. 실수{3} 돌이킬 수 없어요.\n(I miss my hometown. I cannot reverse the mistake.)",blanks:{"1":"을","2":"요","3":"를"},pool:["을","요","를","이","는","에","가","서"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Past modifier. Should-have. Subject.",s:"어렸{1} 때 더 많이 여행{2} 걸. 지금은 시간{3} 없어요.\n(Should have traveled more when young. Now there's no time.)",blanks:{"1":"을","2":"할","3":"이"},pool:["을","할","이","는","한","가","에","의"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"불안하다 vs 걱정하다:\n불안 = anxiety (general unease).\n걱정 = worry (about specific thing).\nWhich is the pattern?\n(Distinguishing worry words.)",opts:["걱정하다 = worry (specific thing); 불안하다 = anxiety (general unease)","Both basic vocabulary","both advanced vocabulary","불안 is basic"],ans:"걱정하다 = worry (specific thing); 불안하다 = anxiety (general unease)",hint:"걱정 appears frequently onward."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l2",title:"할걸",icon:"😩",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"I Should Have...",desc:"-(으)ㄹ걸 (그랬다)\n→ Expressing regret about a past choice.\n\n'I should have studied more.'\n'I should have listened.'",goals:["Use -(으)ㄹ걸 to express regret","Distinguish from -(으)면 좋겠다 (wish)","Build multi-pattern regret sentences"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)ㄹ걸 (그랬다)",src:"I should have... (regret)",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"eul-geol",note:"Expresses regret about a past choice.\nThe speaker wishes they had done differently.\n\nV-(으)ㄹ걸 (casual, to yourself)\nV-(으)ㄹ걸 그랬다 (with emphasis)\n\n먹을걸 = should have eaten\n갈걸 = should have gone",example:"A: 시험 결과 어떠셨어요? B: 떨어졌어요. 더 열심히 공부할걸. A: 아쉽겠다. 많이 준비 안 했어요? B: 시간이 부족했어요. 미리 시작할걸 그랬어요. A: 어떤 과목이 어려웠어요? B: 문법이요. 문법책을 더 볼걸. A: 다음에는 스터디 그룹에 참가해 보세요. B: 좋은 생각이에요. 혼자 공부 안 할걸 그랬어요. A: 다음 시험은 언제예요? B: 석 달 후요. 이번에는 일찍 시작할 거예요.",exampleSrc:"A: How was your test result? B: I failed. I should have studied harder. A: That must be disappointing. Didn't you prepare much? B: I didn't have enough time. I should have started earlier. A: Which subject was hard? B: Grammar. I should have reviewed the grammar book more. A: Next time try joining a study group. B: Good idea. I shouldn't have studied alone. A: When is the next exam? B: In three months. This time I'll start early.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"verb_table",title:"-(으)ㄹ걸 Usage",note:"Always about YOUR OWN past actions.\nCannot be used for other people's actions.",deepDive:{
          title:"Regret Expression Comparison",
          text:"-(으)ㄹ걸 = should have (mild regret, casual)\n 공부할걸. (Should've studied.)\n\n-았/었어야 했는데 = should have (stronger regret)\n 공부했어야 했는데. (Should have studied.)\n\n-았/었더라면 = if I had (counterfactual)\n 공부했더라면 합격했을 텐데.\n (If I had studied, I would have passed.)\n\nEach builds on the next in intensity.\nYou'll learn -았/었더라면 later in this unit."
        },groups:[
          {
            label:"Regretting what you DIDN'T do",
            rows:[{pronoun:"공부할걸.",form:"Should have studied.",src:""},{pronoun:"일찍 올걸.",form:"Should have come early.",src:""}]
          },
          {
            label:"Regretting what you DID do",
            rows:[{pronoun:"안 먹을걸.",form:"Shouldn't have eaten.",src:""},{pronoun:"말 안 할걸.",form:"Shouldn't have said it.",src:""}]
          }
        ],label:"Two Situations"},
        {type:"mc",q:"더 열심히 공부할걸.\nThe speaker is expressing:",opts:["Regret about not studying harder","A plan to study harder","A wish for the future","Advice to someone else"],ans:"Regret about not studying harder",hint:"-(으)ㄹ걸 = I should have. Past regret."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["올걸","오면","와서","오니까"],hint:"Should have brought. Regret ending.",s:"우산을 가져{1}. 비가 올 줄 몰랐어.\n(I should have brought an umbrella. Didn't know it would rain.)",a:"올걸"},
        {type:"mc",q:"말 안 할걸 그랬다.\nWhat does this mean?",opts:["I shouldn't have said it (regret speaking)","I should have spoken up","I want to say something","I didn't say anything"],ans:"I shouldn't have said it (regret speaking)",hint:"안 negates the action. Combined with the regret ending, what does that mean about speaking?"},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Should have come. Bittersweet feeling adjective stem.",s:"일찍 {1}. 늦어서 {2}워요.\n(I should have come early. I'm late so it's a shame.)",blanks:{"1":"올걸","2":"아쉬"},pool:["올걸","아쉬","오면","후회"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which CANNOT use -(으)ㄹ걸?",opts:["친구가 공부할걸 (about someone else's action)","일찍 잘걸 (should have slept early)","안 먹을걸 (shouldn't have eaten)","더 열심히 할걸 (should have tried harder)"],ans:"친구가 공부할걸 (about someone else's action)",hint:"-(으)ㄹ걸 is ONLY for your own actions."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Should have watched. Hearsay ending.",s:"그 영화 {1}걸. 재미있다{2}.\n(I should have watched that movie. I heard it's fun.)",blanks:{"1":"볼","2":"더라"},pool:["볼","더라","본","던데","보는","면서"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Should have come. Lose-hand. Past wish connector.",s:"더 일찍 {1} {2}를 안 했으면 좋았{3} 텐데.\n(Should have come earlier. Wish I hadn't made a mistake.)",blanks:{"1":"올걸.","2":"실수","3":"을"},pool:["올걸.","실수","을","갈걸.","후회","는"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"우산을 가져올걸 그랬다.\n아시다시피 비가 많이 왔습니다.\nU23 + U24 patterns:",opts:["-(으)ㄹ걸 (regret) + 다시피 (as you know)","Only -(으)ㄹ걸","Only 다시피","Neither is a learned pattern"],ans:"-(으)ㄹ걸 (regret) + 다시피 (as you know)",hint:"Regret from U24 + shared knowledge from U23."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Study. After-turn-back. Bittersweet.",s:"{1}할걸. {2}해도 소용없지만 {3}워요.\n(Should have studied harder. Regretting is no use, but it's a shame.)",blanks:{"1":"공부","2":"후회","3":"아쉬"},pool:["공부","후회","아쉬","운동","실수","불안"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Survey. University. Regret. Hearsay. Should have chosen.",s:"{1}에 따르면 {2}생의 70%가 진로 선택을 {3}한다{4} 저도 다른 전공을 {5}\n(According to a survey, 70% of students regret their career choice. I also should have chosen a different major.)",blanks:{"1":"조사","2":"대학","3":"후회","4":"더라.","5":"고를걸."},pool:["조사","대학","후회","더라.","고를걸.","통계","고등학","실수","던데.","골랐으면."]},
        {type:"mc",q:"우산을 가져올걸!\n우산 belongs to which vocabulary?\n(I should have brought an umbrella!)",opts:["Weather/daily items ","academic vocabulary","formal vocabulary","food vocabulary"],ans:"Weather/daily items ",hint:"everyday objects."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Should-have. Subject. Cause (because).",s:"미리 예약{1} 걸. 자리{2} 없어{3}요.\n(I should have reserved in advance. There are no seats.)",blanks:{"1":"할","2":"가","3":"서"},pool:["할","가","서","한","를","어","하","의"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-(으)ㄹ걸 is ONLY for the speaker's OWN past choices.\nWhich sentence is WRONG?\n(Constraint of the regret pattern.)",opts:["네가 공부할걸 (You should have studied) .  WRONG: can't use for others","내가 공부할걸 (I should have studied)","일찍 잘걸 (Should have slept early)","더 먹을걸 (Should have eaten more)"],ans:"네가 공부할걸 (You should have studied) .  WRONG: can't use for others",hint:"-(으)ㄹ걸 is first-person only."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Object. cause (sequential).",s:"택시{1} 탈걸! 버스{2} 타{3}서 늦었어요.\n(Should have taken a taxi! Because I took the bus, I was late.)",blanks:{"1":"를","2":"를","3":"아"},pool:["를","를","아","을","이","어","가","는"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"걸=light. 좋겠다=wish. 더라면=full unreal past.",s:"-(으)ㄹ걸: {1} regret, speaker {2}.\n-(으)면 좋겠다: {3}, any person.\n-았/었더라면: {4} counterfactual.\n(Three levels of wishing.)",blanks:{"1":"mild","2":"only","3":"wish","4":"strong"},pool:["mild","only","wish","strong","heavy","anyone","regret","weak"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Subject. Indirect speech (said it was).",s:"그 영화{1} 볼걸. 친구{2} 재미있{3}고 했어요.\n(Should have watched that movie. My friend said it was fun.)",blanks:{"1":"를","2":"가","3":"다"},pool:["를","가","다","을","는","어","이","라"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Should-have. Subject.",s:"그때 고백{1} 걸. 용기{2} 없었어요.\n(Should have confessed then. I had no courage.)",blanks:{"1":"할","2":"가"},pool:["할","가","한","를","하","이","는","의"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"더 일찍 시작할걸 그랬어요.\n그랬어요 adds what nuance?\n(Should have started earlier, I regret it.)",opts:["Emphasis: reinforces the regret feeling","Changes to present tense","Makes it a question","Removes regret meaning"],ans:"Emphasis: reinforces the regret feeling",hint:"그랬어요 = I should have done so."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l3",title:"할 뻔했다",icon:"😰",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"I Almost Did (Near-Miss)",desc:"-(으)ㄹ 뻔하다 [HARVEST]\n→ You first saw this pattern in A2.\nNow we formally teach it for B2 regret contexts.\n\n'I almost fell.'\n'I nearly missed the train.'",goals:["Use -(으)ㄹ 뻔하다 for near-miss events","Combine with regret patterns from L2","Express relief or regret about what almost happened"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)ㄹ 뻔하다",src:"almost did / nearly (near-miss)",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"eul ppeon-ha-da",note:"HARVEST.\nExpresses something that ALMOST happened but didn't.\n\n뻔하다 = to be obvious/almost\nV-(으)ㄹ 뻔했다 = almost did\n\nUsually for:\n- Dangerous near-misses (relief)\n- Missed opportunities (regret)",example:"A: 왜 이렇게 놀란 표정이에요? B: 아까 길에서 넘어질 뻔했어요! A: 괜찮아요? 다친 데는 없어요? B: 다행히 괜찮아요. 하마터면 큰일 날 뻔했어요. A: 어디서 넘어질 뻔했어요? B: 횡단보도에서요. 바닥이 얼어 있었어요. A: 요즘 빙판길이 많아서 위험해요. B: 맞아요. 하마터면 차에 치일 뻔했어요. A: 미끄럼 방지 신발을 신으세요. B: 네, 내일부터 꼭 신을게요.",exampleSrc:"A: Why do you look so startled? B: I almost fell on the street earlier! A: Are you okay? You're not hurt? B: Fortunately I'm fine. It was almost a disaster. A: Where did you almost fall? B: At the crosswalk. The ground was frozen. A: There are many icy roads these days, so it's dangerous. B: Right. I almost got hit by a car too. A: Wear anti-slip shoes. B: Yes, I'll definitely wear them starting tomorrow.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"tip",title:"뻔하다 Two Moods",deepDive:"Extended forms:\n\n-(으)ㄹ 뻔했다: basic near-miss\n 죽을 뻔했어! (I almost died!)\n\n하마터면 + -(으)ㄹ 뻔했다: emphasis\n 하마터면 늦을 뻔했어요.\n (I was THIS close to being late.)\n\n-(으)ㄹ 뻔하지 않았다: denial of near-miss\n 위험할 뻔하지 않았어요.\n (It wasn't even close to dangerous.)\n\n하마터면 adds dramatic emphasis.\nVery common in storytelling.",text:"The same pattern, two emotions:\n\nRelief (dangerous near-miss):\n 차에 치일 뻔했어요!\n (I almost got hit by a car!)\n → Thank goodness it didn't happen!\n\nRegret (missed opportunity):\n 합격할 뻔했는데...\n (I almost passed, but...)\n → So close! What a shame.\n\nContext determines the emotion.\nThe grammar is identical."},
        {type:"mc",q:"넘어질 뻔했어요!\nThe speaker:",opts:["Almost fell but didn't (relief)","Actually fell","Plans to fall","Wants to fall"],ans:"Almost fell but didn't (relief)",hint:"뻔했다 = almost did. Didn't actually happen."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["칠","친","치는","칠까"],hint:"Almost missed. Future/potential form of 놓치다.",s:"하마터면 비행기를 놓{1} 뻔했어요.\n(I was THIS close to missing the flight.)",a:"칠"},
        {type:"mc",q:"합격할 뻔했는데 아쉬워요.\nThe speaker's emotion:",opts:["Regret (almost passed but didn't)","Relief (almost passed)","Joy (actually passed)","Indifference"],ans:"Regret (almost passed but didn't)",hint:"뻔했는데 + 아쉽다 = almost happened, what a shame."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["실수","후회","불안","아쉬움"],hint:"Lose-hand: a slip. Near-miss + relief.",s:"큰 {1}를 할 뻔했어요. 다행이에요.\n(I almost made a big mistake. That's a relief.)",a:"실수"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which pairs regret + near-miss?\nA: 공부할걸. 합격할 뻔했는데.\nB: 공부했어요. 합격했어요.",opts:["A expresses regret about a near-miss","B expresses regret about a near-miss","Both express regret","Neither expresses regret"],ans:"A expresses regret about a near-miss",hint:"Look for the pair that combines a wish to change the past with an almost-happened event."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Vehicle. Passive hit form before 뻔하다.",s:"하마터면 {1}에 치{2} 뻔했어요!\n(I was almost hit by a car!)",blanks:{"1":"차","2":"일"},pool:["차","일","기차","을","버스","는"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Study. Failure. Connector. Bittersweet.",s:"더 {1}할걸. 하마터면 {2}할 뻔했{3} {4}워요.\n(Should have studied more. I was almost about to fail. It's a shame.)",blanks:{"1":"공부","2":"불합격","3":"는데","4":"아쉬"},pool:["공부","불합격","는데","아쉬","운동","합격","어서","후회"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"사고로 인해 길이 막혔습니다.\n하마터면 늦을 뻔했어요.\nRegister shift:",opts:["First is formal news; second is casual personal","Both are formal","Both are casual","First is casual; second is formal"],ans:"First is formal news; second is casual personal",hint:"으로 인해 = news. 뻔했어요 = personal storytelling."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"News. Accident. Hearsay. Same word again for personal near-miss.",s:"{1}에 따르면 {2}가 심각하다{3} 저도 {4}를 할 뻔했어요.\n(According to reports, accidents are serious, I heard. I also almost had an accident.)",blanks:{"1":"보도","2":"사고","3":"더라.","4":"사고"},pool:["보도","사고","더라.","사고","통계","실수","던데.","피해"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Chance. Almost miss. But. Pass. Should have come.",s:"{1}를 놓{2} 뻔했{3} 다행히 {4}했어요. 다음에는 일찍 {5}\n(I almost missed the opportunity, but fortunately succeeded. Next time I should come early.)",blanks:{"1":"기회","2":"칠","3":"지만","4":"합격","5":"올걸."},pool:["기회","칠","지만","합격","올걸.","비행기","친","는데","불합격","갈걸."]},
        {type:"mc",q:"하마터면 넘어질 뻔했어요!\n넘어지다 means?\n(I almost fell!)",opts:["넘어지다 = to fall down ","넘어지다 = to jump","넘어지다 = to climb","넘어지다 = to run"],ans:"넘어지다 = to fall down ",hint:"physical motion vocabulary."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Past polite. Almost-did.",s:"버스{1} 놓칠 뻔했{2}요! 하마터면 지각{3} 뻔했어요.\n(Almost missed the bus! Almost was late.)",blanks:{"1":"를","2":"어","3":"할"},pool:["를","어","할","을","아","하","이","에"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-(으)ㄹ 뻔하다 is harvested.\nThe form expresses?\n(Reviewing the near-miss pattern.)",opts:["Relief that something bad almost happened but didn't","Certainty it will happen","Regret about past","Wish for future"],ans:"Relief that something bad almost happened but didn't",hint:"Near-miss: it almost happened but was avoided."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Past (fortunately held). Modifier (near-miss).",s:"비밀{1} 말할 뻔했어요. 다행히 참{2}어요. 위험할 뻔{3} 상황이었어요.\n(Almost told the secret. Fortunately held back. It was a near-dangerous situation.)",blanks:{"1":"을","2":"았","3":"한"},pool:["을","았","한","이","어","하","는","의"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"뻔하다=phew! 걸=wish I had. Both use ㄹ modifier.",s:"-(으)ㄹ 뻔하다: near-miss, speaker feels {1}.\n-(으)ㄹ걸: past action, speaker feels {2}.\nBoth use -(으)ㄹ {3} modifier.\n(Comparing two past-oriented patterns.)",blanks:{"1":"relief","2":"regret","3":"future/prospective"},pool:["relief","regret","future/prospective","fear","hope","past","present","anger"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Subject. Past polite. Object. cause.",s:"사고{1} 날 뻔했{2}요. 안전벨트{3} 하{4}서 다행이에요.\n(There was almost an accident. Fortunately I wore a seatbelt.)",blanks:{"1":"가","2":"어","3":"를","4":"아"},pool:["가","어","를","아","이","았","을","는"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"할 뻔했다 + 할걸 combined:\n하마터면 실수할 뻔했어요. 미리 확인할걸!\nWhat grammar patterns are combined here?\n(Almost made a mistake. Should have checked!)",opts:["2: 뻔하다 (near-miss) + -(으)ㄹ걸 (regret)","1 pattern","3 patterns","0 patterns"],ans:"2: 뻔하다 (near-miss) + -(으)ㄹ걸 (regret)",hint:"뻔하다 was seed, now depth. 걸 is new."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Almost-didn't. Subject. Explaining why (거든요).",s:"전화{1} 안 받{2} 뻔했어요. 벨소리{3} 안 들렸거든{4}.\n(Almost didn't answer the phone. Because I couldn't hear the ringtone.)",blanks:{"1":"를","2":"을","3":"가","4":"요"},pool:["를","을","가","요","이","는","에","어"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"하마터면 adds what nuance to -(으)ㄹ 뻔하다?\n(The emphasis word before near-miss.)",opts:["Dramatic emphasis: by a hair's breadth","Softens the near-miss","Makes it formal","Changes to future tense"],ans:"Dramatic emphasis: by a hair's breadth",hint:"하마터면 = nearly/by a narrow margin."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l4",title:"텐데 vs 테니까",icon:"🔮",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Expectations & Conditional Promises",desc:"-(으)ㄹ 텐데 vs -(으)ㄹ 테니(까)\n→ Two related but different patterns.\n\n텐데: I expect / it would probably be...\n테니까: since it will be... / I promise to...",goals:["Use -(으)ㄹ 텐데 for expectations and regret","Use -(으)ㄹ 테니까 for promises and reasons","Distinguish the two in conversation"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)ㄹ 텐데",src:"it would probably... / I expect that...",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"eul ten-de",note:"Expectation + concern or regret.\n텐데 = 터인데 (expected situation + but/so)\n\nTwo uses:\n1. Concern: 힘들 텐데 괜찮아요?\n (It must be hard, are you okay?)\n2. Regret: 갔으면 좋았을 텐데.\n (It would have been good if I'd gone.)",example:"A: 어제 야근했다면서요? B: 네, 새벽 두 시까지 일했어요. A: 피곤할 텐데 오늘은 좀 쉬세요. B: 쉬고 싶지만 회의가 있어요. A: 힘들 텐데 괜찮아요? B: 솔직히 좀 힘들어요. 하지만 어쩔 수 없어요. A: 점심 때라도 잠깐 쉬세요. B: 네, 회의 끝나면 낮잠 잘게요. A: 건강이 제일 중요하니까 무리하지 마세요. B: 고마워요. 오늘만 버티면 돼요.",exampleSrc:"A: I heard you worked overtime yesterday? B: Yes, I worked until 2 AM. A: You must be tired, so please rest today. B: I want to rest but I have a meeting. A: It must be hard. Are you okay? B: Honestly it's a bit tough. But I have no choice. A: At least take a short rest during lunch. B: Yes, I'll take a nap after the meeting. A: Health is most important, so don't overdo it. B: Thank you. I just need to get through today.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)ㄹ 테니(까)",src:"since I will... / because it will be...",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"eul te-ni-kka",note:"Promise or confident prediction as reason.\n테니까 = 터이니까 (will be the case, so...)\n\n1. Promise: 내가 할 테니까 가 봐.\n (I'll do it, so go ahead.)\n2. Prediction: 비가 올 테니까 우산 가져가.\n (It'll rain, so take an umbrella.)",example:"A: 이 짐 너무 무거워요. 어떻게 옮기죠? B: 제가 도와줄 테니까 걱정하지 마세요. A: 정말요? 감사합니다. B: 차를 가져올 테니까 여기서 기다리세요. A: 비가 올 것 같은데 괜찮을까요? B: 금방 올 테니까 비 맞을 일은 없을 거예요. A: 우산도 가져올까요? B: 아니요, 제가 가져올 테니까 신경 쓰지 마세요. A: 정말 고마워요. 많이 도와주시네요. B: 별말씀요. 친구니까 당연하죠.",exampleSrc:"A: This luggage is too heavy. How do we move it? B: I'll help you, so don't worry. A: Really? Thank you. B: I'll bring the car, so wait here. A: It looks like it might rain. Will it be okay? B: I'll be back quickly, so there's no chance of getting rained on. A: Should I bring an umbrella too? B: No, I'll bring one, so don't worry about it. A: Really thank you. You're helping so much. B: Don't mention it. Of course, since we're friends.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"tip",title:"텐데 vs 테니까",deepDive:"Past forms for counterfactuals:\n\n-았/었을 텐데: would have been\n 합격했을 텐데. (Would've passed.)\n → Regret about an unrealized outcome.\n\n-았/었을 테니까: since it would have been\n 힘들었을 테니까 쉬어. (Since it must've been hard, rest.)\n → Empathy based on past assumption.\n\nThe past counterfactual 텐데 is very common\nin expressing what COULD have happened:\n 공부했으면 합격했을 텐데.\n (If I'd studied, I would've passed.)",text:"텐데: expectation + follow-up concern\n 바쁘실 텐데 감사합니다.\n (You must be busy, but thank you.)\n Speaker GUESSES the situation.\n\n테니까: confident prediction as REASON\n 곧 끝날 테니까 기다려.\n (It'll end soon, so wait.)\n Speaker gives a REASON for an action.\n\nTip: 텐데 often leads to sympathy.\n테니까 often leads to a command/suggestion."},
        {type:"mc",q:"피곤할 텐데 좀 쉬세요.\nThe speaker is:",opts:["Showing concern based on an expectation","Making a promise","Expressing regret","Reporting hearsay"],ans:"Showing concern based on an expectation",hint:"텐데 = I expect/assume + concern."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["줄","준","주는","줄까"],hint:"Future/promise form before 테니까.",s:"제가 도와{1} 테니까 걱정하지 마세요.\n(I'll help you, so don't worry.)",a:"줄"},
        {type:"mc",q:"합격했을 텐데...\nThis expresses:",opts:["Regret: would have passed (but didn't)","Certainty: definitely passed","Promise: will pass","Question: did they pass?"],ans:"Regret: would have passed (but didn't)",hint:"The sentence trails off with ... suggesting something that did NOT actually happen. What emotion does that carry?"},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Rain future form. Go (casual command).",s:"비가 {1} 테니까 우산 가져{2}.\n(It'll rain, so take an umbrella.)",blanks:{"1":"올","2":"가"},pool:["올","가","오는","가는","온","간"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"바쁘실 텐데 시간 내 주셔서 감사합니다.\n텐데 is followed by:",opts:["Gratitude despite the expected situation","A command","A question","A promise"],ans:"Gratitude despite the expected situation",hint:"You must be busy (텐데) BUT thank you for making time."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Pass. Regret ending.",s:"공부했으면 {1}했을 텐데. 공부{2}걸.\n(If I'd studied, I would've passed. Should've studied.)",blanks:{"1":"합격","2":"할"},pool:["합격","할","불합격","안 할"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Hard. Endure politely. End future form.",s:"힘{1} 텐데 조금만 더 {2}. 곧 끝{3} 테니까.\n(It must be hard, but hang in just a bit more. It'll end soon.)",blanks:{"1":"들","2":"버텨요","3":"날"},pool:["들","버텨요","날","든","쉬세요","나는"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"내가 다 할 테니까 넌 가.\n테니까 here expresses:",opts:["A promise as reason: I'll do it, so you go","An expectation: it must be done","Regret: I should have done it","Hearsay: I heard it was done"],ans:"A promise as reason: I'll do it, so you go",hint:"Speaker promises (할 테니까) + gives suggestion (가)."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Near-miss form. But connector. Fine/okay.",s:"놓{1} 뻔했{2} 다행히 {3}을 텐데.\n(Almost missed it, but fortunately it will be okay.)",blanks:{"1":"칠","2":"지만","3":"괜찮"},pool:["칠","지만","괜찮","친","는데","힘들"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Study. Pass. Study again (regret). Help promise.",s:"{1}했으면 {2}했을 텐데 {3}할걸. 다음에는 제가 도와{4} 테니까 걱정 마세요.\n(If I'd studied, I would've passed. Should've studied. Next time I'll help, so don't worry.)",blanks:{"1":"공부","2":"합격","3":"공부","4":"줄"},pool:["공부","합격","공부","줄","운동","불합격","운동","준"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Expectation modifier. Subject (I).",s:"피곤하{1} 텐데 좀 쉬세요. 제{2} 할 테니까 걱정 마세요.\n(You must be tired, so rest. I will do it, so don't worry.)",blanks:{"1":"ㄹ","2":"가"},pool:["ㄹ","가","을","는","이","에","를","의"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-았/었을 텐데: past counterfactual concern.\n미리 말했으면 도와줬을 텐데.\n-(으)면 means?\n(If you had told me, I would have helped.)",opts:["-(으)면 = if/when ","-(으)면 = because","-(으)면 = although","-(으)면 = while"],ans:"-(으)면 = if/when ",hint:"conditional that builds the counterfactual."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Expectation. Adverbial. Object. Honorific.",s:"내일 춥{1} 텐데 따뜻하{2} 옷{3} 입{4}세요.\n(It will probably be cold tomorrow, so wear warm clothes.)",blanks:{"1":"을","2":"게","3":"을","4":"으"},pool:["을","게","을","으","는","이","를","에"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Expectation. Purpose (go to eat). Subject (I).",s:"배고프{1} 텐데 밥 먹{2}러 갈까요? 제{3} 살 테니까 걱정 마세요.\n(You must be hungry, shall we go eat? I'll pay so don't worry.)",blanks:{"1":"ㄹ","2":"으","3":"가"},pool:["ㄹ","으","가","을","는","이","에","를"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-(으)ㄹ 텐데 vs -(으)ㄹ 테니까:\n텐데 = concern for LISTENER.\n테니까 = SPEAKER's promise/plan as reason.\nWhich expresses empathy?\n(Comparing the two patterns.)",opts:["텐데 expresses empathy and concern","테니까 expresses empathy","Both express empathy equally","Neither expresses empathy"],ans:"텐데 expresses empathy and concern",hint:"텐데 = I imagine you might be X (caring)."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"If alone. Lonely (expectation). Let's. Object (road).",s:"혼자{1}면 외로{2} 텐데 같이 가{3}요. 길{4} 안내할 테니까요.\n(You'd be lonely alone, let's go together. I'll guide the way.)",blanks:{"1":"이","2":"울","3":"자","4":"을"},pool:["이","울","자","을","는","는","ㅂ시","를"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"힘들었을 텐데 잘 해냈어요!\n-았/었을 텐데 is past + expectation.\n-아/어 내다 means?\n(It must have been hard but you did great!)",opts:["-아/어 내다 = to accomplish/manage to do ","내다 = to put out","내다 = to start","내다 = to forget"],ans:"-아/어 내다 = to accomplish/manage to do ",hint:"completion auxiliary: successfully did."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l5",title:"했더라면",icon:"⏪",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"If I Had Done...",desc:"-았/었더라면\n→ The Korean 'if only I had...'\n\nThe most powerful regret pattern.\nDescribes an UNREAL past and its imagined result.",goals:["Use -았/었더라면 for past counterfactuals","Combine with -(으)ㄹ 텐데 for imagined results","Build full counterfactual regret sentences"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-았/었더라면",src:"if (I/they) had done... (past counterfactual)",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"at-deo-ra-myeon",note:"Past counterfactual condition.\nThe action did NOT happen.\nImagining a different past.\n\nStructure:\nV-았/었더라면 + result + (으)ㄹ 텐데\n\n했더라면 = if (I) had done\n갔더라면 = if (I) had gone\n알았더라면 = if (I) had known",example:"A: 비행기를 놓쳤어요. B: 왜요? 무슨 일이 있었어요? A: 택시가 늦게 왔어요. 일찍 출발했더라면 늦지 않았을 텐데. B: 그 전날 미리 준비했더라면 좋았을 텐데요. A: 알람을 더 일찍 맞췄더라면 이런 일이 없었을 거예요. B: 공항 근처에서 잤더라면 편했을 텐데. A: 맞아요. 다음부터는 전날에 짐을 싸 놓을게요. B: 다음 비행기는 몇 시예요? A: 세 시간 후에 있어요. 기다릴 수밖에 없어요. B: 카페에서 기다리면서 쉬세요.",exampleSrc:"A: I missed the flight. B: Why? What happened? A: The taxi came late. If I had left early, I wouldn't have been late. B: It would have been good if you had prepared the day before. A: If I had set my alarm earlier, this wouldn't have happened. B: If you had slept near the airport, it would have been easier. A: You're right. From now on I'll pack my bags the night before. B: What time is the next flight? A: In three hours. I have no choice but to wait. B: Rest at a cafe while you wait.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"verb_table",title:"Full Counterfactual Chain",note:"Each is progressively stronger.\n-았/었더라면 is the STRONGEST regret form.",deepDive:{
          title:"Common Counterfactual Pairs",
          text:"-았/었더라면 + -(으)ㄹ 텐데\n 공부했더라면 합격했을 텐데.\n (If studied, would've passed.)\n\n-았/었더라면 + -았/었을 거예요\n 일찍 갔더라면 만났을 거예요.\n (If left early, would've met them.)\n\n-았/었더라면 + 안 -았/었을 텐데\n 조심했더라면 사고가 안 났을 텐데.\n (If careful, accident wouldn't have happened.)\n\nThe result clause is ALWAYS about an unreal outcome.\nSomething that did NOT happen."
        },groups:[
          {label:"1. Simple Wish (future/present)",rows:[{pronoun:"갔으면 좋겠어요.",form:"I wish I could go.",src:"mild"}]},
          {label:"2. Past Regret (mild)",rows:[{pronoun:"갈걸.",form:"Should have gone.",src:"casual"}]},
          {label:"3. Counterfactual (strong)",rows:[{pronoun:"갔더라면 좋았을 텐데.",form:"If I had gone, it would've been good.",src:"formal"}]}
        ],label:"Regret Progression (Weak → Strong)"},
        {type:"mc",q:"일찍 출발했더라면 늦지 않았을 텐데.\nWhat happened in reality?",opts:["Left late and was late (regret)","Left early and was on time","Left early but was still late","Didn't leave at all"],ans:"Left late and was late (regret)",hint:"Counterfactual: the opposite happened. They DID leave late."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Advance preparation. Lose-hand error.",s:"미리 {1}했더라면 이런 {2}는 안 했을 텐데.\n(If I had prepared in advance, I wouldn't have made this mistake.)",blanks:{"1":"준비","2":"실수"},pool:["준비","실수","후회","불안","공부","아쉬움"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"알았더라면 도와줬을 텐데.\nThe speaker:",opts:["Didn't know, so couldn't help (regret)","Knew and helped","Doesn't want to help","Will help in the future"],ans:"Didn't know, so couldn't help (regret)",hint:"알았더라면 = if I had known. But I didn't."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Making a choice. Not-peace feeling.",s:"그때 {1}했더라면 지금 {2}하지 않았을 텐데.\n(If I had decided then, I wouldn't be anxious now.)",blanks:{"1":"결정","2":"불안"},pool:["결정","불안","후회","실수","선택","아쉬움"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"합격할 뻔했는데. 더 공부했더라면 합격했을 텐데.\nTwo patterns combined:",opts:["뻔하다 (almost) + 더라면/텐데 (if had, would have)","Only 뻔하다","Only 더라면","Neither is a regret pattern"],ans:"뻔하다 (almost) + 더라면/텐데 (if had, would have)",hint:"Near-miss + counterfactual = powerful regret combination."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Brought (past). Wouldn't have. Should have.",s:"우산을 가져{1}더라면 비에 안 맞{2} 텐데. 가져{3}.\n(If I'd brought an umbrella, I wouldn't have gotten rained on. Should've brought it.)",blanks:{"1":"왔","2":"았을","3":"올걸"},pool:["왔","았을","올걸","오면","을","오면"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Specialists. Advance prep. Hearsay. Same word. Not-peace.",s:"{1}에 따르면 조기 {2}가 중요하다{3} 미리 {4}했더라면 {5}가 줄었을 텐데.\n(According to experts, early preparation is important. If I had prepared in advance, anxiety would have decreased.)",blanks:{"1":"전문가","2":"준비","3":"더라.","4":"준비","5":"불안"},pool:["전문가","준비","더라.","준비","불안","통계","공부","던데.","공부","후회"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Rank the regret intensity:\nA: 갈걸.\nB: 갔더라면 좋았을 텐데.\nC: 가고 싶었어요.",opts:["C (weakest: wish) < A (mild regret) < B (strongest: counterfactual)","A < B < C","B < A < C","All equal"],ans:"C (weakest: wish) < A (mild regret) < B (strongest: counterfactual)",hint:"Wish < should have < if I had gone, it would have been..."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Almost-miss form. But. After-turn-back.",s:"그 기회를 놓{1} 뻔했{2} 잡았더라면 지금 {3}하지 않았을 텐데.\n(I almost missed that opportunity. If I had grabbed it, I wouldn't regret now.)",blanks:{"1":"칠","2":"지만","3":"후회"},pool:["칠","지만","후회","친","는데","실수"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Study. Pass. Study (regret). Almost miss.",s:"{1}했더라면 {2}했을 텐데. {3}할걸. 하마터면 기회를 완전히 놓{4} 뻔했어요.\n(If I had studied, I would have passed. Should have studied. I almost completely missed the chance.)",blanks:{"1":"공부","2":"합격","3":"공부","4":"칠"},pool:["공부","합격","공부","칠","운동","불합격","운동","친"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"그때 더 공부했더라면 합격했을 텐데.\nThis combines which TWO patterns?\n(If I had studied more, I would have passed.)",opts:["-았/었더라면 (counterfactual if) + -(으)ㄹ 텐데 (would have)","Only one pattern","Three patterns","unrelated patterns"],ans:"-았/었더라면 (counterfactual if) + -(으)ㄹ 텐데 (would have)",hint:"Full counterfactual chain: if-had + would-have."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Counterfactual past. Object. Would-have.",s:"일찍 출발했{1}라면 비행기{2} 탔{3} 텐데.\n(If I had left early, I would have caught the plane.)",blanks:{"1":"더","2":"를","3":"을"},pool:["더","를","을","어","을","이","는","가"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-았/었더라면 is the STRONGEST hypothetical.\n걸 < 면 좋겠다 < 더라면.\nWhat does 면 좋겠다 express?\n(Ranking the regret/wish patterns.)",opts:["-(으)면 좋겠다 (wish)","basic sentence ending","polite request form","advanced connector"],ans:"-(으)면 좋겠다 (wish)",hint:"wish expression."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Target. Would-have. Polite.",s:"한국어{1} 열심히 배웠더라면 TOPIK{2} 통과했{3} 텐데. 아쉬워{4}.\n(If I had studied Korean hard, I would have passed TOPIK. Regretful.)",blanks:{"1":"를","2":"에","3":"을","4":"요"},pool:["를","에","을","요","을","이","는","서"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"걸=light, self only. 더라면=full unreal, anyone.",s:"-(으)ㄹ걸: {1} regret, {2} person only.\n-았/었더라면: {3} counterfactual, {4} person.\n(Comparing regret levels.)",blanks:{"1":"mild","2":"first","3":"strong","4":"any"},pool:["mild","first","strong","any","heavy","second","weak","third"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Would-have. nobody.",s:"그 소식{1} 들었더라면 갔{2} 텐데. 아무{3} 안 알려줬어요.\n(If I had heard the news, I would have gone. Nobody told me.)",blanks:{"1":"을","2":"을","3":"도"},pool:["을","을","도","이","는","가","에","를"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"매일 운동했더라면 건강했을 텐데.\n매일 means?\n(If I had exercised every day, I would have been healthy.)",opts:["매일 = every day ","매일 = sometimes","매일 = never","매일 = often"],ans:"매일 = every day ",hint:"frequency/time vocabulary."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l6",title:"할까 봐",icon:"😟",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Worried That Might...",desc:"-(으)ㄹ까 봐 / -(으)ㄹ까 말까\n→ Expressing worry and indecision.\n\n까 봐: worried that something might happen\n까 말까: whether to do or not (torn)",goals:["Use -(으)ㄹ까 봐 for worry/anxiety","Use -(으)ㄹ까 말까 for indecision","Combine with other regret patterns"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)ㄹ까 봐",src:"worried/afraid that might...",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"eul-kka bwa",note:"Expresses worry about a possible event.\n까 = question marker\n봐 = in case (looking at possibility)\n\nV-(으)ㄹ까 봐 + preventive action\n 늦을까 봐 일찍 나왔어요.\n (Came out early worried I'd be late.)",example:"A: 오늘 날씨가 이상하네요. B: 그래서 비가 올까 봐 우산을 가져왔어요. A: 잘했어요. 저는 안 가져왔어요. B: 같이 쓸까요? 우산이 크거든요. A: 고마워요. 비가 안 오면 좋겠는데. B: 일기예보에서 오후에 비 온다고 했어요. A: 그러면 옷이 젖을까 봐 걱정이에요. B: 비닐 가방에 넣으면 돼요. A: 그래도 길이 미끄러울까 봐 불안해요. B: 천천히 걸으면 괜찮을 거예요.",exampleSrc:"A: The weather looks strange today. B: That's why I brought an umbrella worried it might rain. A: Good thinking. I didn't bring one. B: Shall we share? My umbrella is big. A: Thank you. I hope it doesn't rain though. B: The weather forecast said it would rain in the afternoon. A: Then I'm worried my clothes might get wet. B: You can put them in a plastic bag. A: Still, I'm anxious the road might be slippery. B: It'll be fine if we walk slowly.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)ㄹ까 말까",src:"whether to do or not (indecision)",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"eul-kka mal-kka",note:"Expressing indecision/hesitation.\n까 = should I?\n말까 = or not?\n\nV-(으)ㄹ까 말까 (하다)\n 살까 말까 고민해요.\n (Debating whether to buy or not.)",example:"A: 주말에 등산 갈 거예요? B: 갈까 말까 고민 중이에요. A: 왜 고민해요? 날씨가 좋잖아요. B: 다리가 좀 아파서요. 무리할까 봐 걱정이에요. A: 그러면 가벼운 코스로 가요. B: 음, 그래도 할까 말까 모르겠어요. A: 일단 가서 안 되면 돌아오면 돼요. B: 맞아요. 너무 많이 고민하는 것 같아요. A: 안 가면 후회할 수도 있어요. B: 좋아요. 결정했어요. 같이 가요!",exampleSrc:"A: Are you going hiking this weekend? B: I'm debating whether to go or not. A: Why are you hesitating? The weather is nice. B: My leg hurts a bit. I'm worried about overdoing it. A: Then let's take an easy trail. B: Hmm, I still don't know whether to do it or not. A: Just go and if it doesn't work out, we can turn back. B: You're right. I think I'm overthinking it. A: If you don't go, you might regret it. B: Okay. I've decided. Let's go together!",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"tip",title:"까 봐 vs 까 말까",deepDive:"까 봐 with worry vocabulary:\n\n걱정되다 + -(으)ㄹ까 봐\n 시험에 떨어질까 봐 걱정돼요.\n (Worried about failing the exam.)\n\n불안하다 + -(으)ㄹ까 봐\n 실수할까 봐 불안해요.\n (Anxious about making a mistake.)\n\n두렵다 + -(으)ㄹ까 봐\n 혼날까 봐 두려워요.\n (Afraid of getting scolded.)\n\nAll express anxiety about future possibility.\n까 봐 is about prevention; the worry motivates action.",text:"까 봐: worry about a bad outcome\n 실패할까 봐 걱정이에요.\n (Worried I might fail.)\n → Focus: something BAD might happen\n\n까 말까: torn between choices\n 말할까 말까 고민 중이에요.\n (Debating whether to say it or not.)\n → Focus: CAN'T DECIDE\n\n까 봐 leads to preventive actions.\n까 말까 leads to deliberation."},
        {type:"mc",q:"비가 올까 봐 우산을 가져왔어요.\nThe speaker:",opts:["Brought an umbrella as a precaution against rain","Is certain it will rain","Doesn't care about rain","Wants it to rain"],ans:"Brought an umbrella as a precaution against rain",hint:"까 봐 = worried that. Preventive action follows."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["을","는","은","었"],hint:"Future possibility form before 까 봐.",s:"늦{1}까 봐 일찍 나왔어요.\n(Came out early worried I'd be late.)",a:"을"},
        {type:"mc",q:"갈까 말까 고민 중이에요.\nThe speaker is:",opts:["Undecided about whether to go","Decided to go","Decided not to go","Not interested in going"],ans:"Undecided about whether to go",hint:"까 말까 = whether to or not. Still deciding."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["실패","합격","후회","성공"],hint:"Negative outcome that motivates studying.",s:"{1}할까 봐 열심히 공부했어요.\n(Studied hard worried about failing.)",a:"실패"},
        {type:"mc",q:"말할까 말까 하다가 결국 말했어요.\nWhat happened?",opts:["Debated then finally spoke","Decided not to speak","Still deciding","Spoke immediately without hesitation"],ans:"Debated then finally spoke",hint:"까 말까 하다가 = debating, then 결국 = in the end."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Error. Not-peace. Challenge/attempt.",s:"{1}할까 봐 {2}해요. {3}할까 말까 고민 중이에요.\n(Worried about making a mistake, I'm anxious. Debating whether to try or not.)",blanks:{"1":"실수","2":"불안","3":"도전"},pool:["실수","불안","도전","후회","아쉬움","포기"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Rain possibility. Bring possibility. Bring or not. Connector.",s:"비가 {1}까 봐 우산을 가져{2} 안 가져{3}까 말까 고민했{4} 결국 가져왔어요.\n(Worried it might rain, debated whether to bring an umbrella or not. In the end, brought it.)",blanks:{"1":"올","2":"올","3":"올","4":"는데"},pool:["올","올","올","는데","오는","온","온","지만"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"실수할까 봐 불안했는데 했더라면 더 좋았을 텐데.\nPatterns combined:",opts:["까 봐 (worry) + 더라면/텐데 (counterfactual)","Only 까 봐","Only 더라면","까 말까 + 텐데"],ans:"까 봐 (worry) + 더라면/텐데 (counterfactual)",hint:"Was worried + if I had done it, would've been better."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Miss. Apply. But. Advance work.",s:"기회를 놓{1}까 봐 빨리 {2}했{3} {4}했더라면 더 좋았을 텐데.\n(Applied quickly worried about missing the chance. If I had prepared, it would've been better.)",blanks:{"1":"칠","2":"지원","3":"지만","4":"준비"},pool:["칠","지원","지만","준비","친","포기","는데","공부"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"비가 올까 봐 우산을 가져왔어요.\n가져오다 means?\n(Worried it might rain, I brought an umbrella.)",opts:["가져오다 = to bring ","가져오다 = to take away","가져오다 = to lose","가져오다 = to forget"],ans:"가져오다 = to bring ",hint:"가지다 + 오다 compound."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Target (fail AT). Deliberating.",s:"시험{1} 떨어질까 봐 걱정이에요. 갈까 말까 고민{2} 있어요.\n(Worried about failing the exam. I'm debating whether to go or not.)",blanks:{"1":"에","2":"하고"},pool:["에","하고","을","에서","이","하는","가","의"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-(으)ㄹ까 봐 vs -(으)ㄹ까 말까:\n봐 = worry about happening.\n말까 = decide whether to do.\nKey structural difference?\n(Worry vs indecision.)",opts:["까 봐: anxious about future event; 까 말까: deliberate choice to make","Same meaning","까 봐 = positive; 까 말까 = negative","까 말까 is more formal"],ans:"까 봐: anxious about future event; 까 말까: deliberate choice to make",hint:"봐=fear. 말까=should I or shouldn't I."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Future modifier (worry). Object (x2). Subject (ended up).",s:"늦{1}까 봐 택시{2} 탔어요. 택시{2} 탈까 말까 하다{3} 결국 탔어요.\n(Worried about being late, took a taxi. Was debating whether to take a taxi, ended up taking it.)",blanks:{"1":"을","2":"를","3":"가"},pool:["을","를","가","는","을","이","에","의"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Worried about injury, so was careful. Debating whether to say.",s:"-(으)ㄹ까 봐 + preventive: 다칠까 봐 {1}.\n-(으)ㄹ까 말까 + decision: 말할까 말까 {2}.\n(Worry leads to action. Indecision leads to choice.)",blanks:{"1":"조심했어요","2":"고민했어요"},pool:["조심했어요","고민했어요","포기했어요","시작했어요"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Subject (hon.). Past polite. Past modifier.",s:"부모님{1} 걱정하실까 봐 말 안 했{2}요. 아프{3} 걸 숨겼어요.\n(Worried my parents would worry, I didn't tell them. I hid that I was sick.)",blanks:{"1":"이","2":"어","3":"ㄴ"},pool:["이","어","ㄴ","을","아","는","가","의"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Future (worry about). Emphasis (as many as). Still/even.",s:"실수{1}까 봐 세 번{2}나 확인했어요. 그래{3} 걱정이에요.\n(Worried about making a mistake, I checked three times. Still, I'm worried.)",blanks:{"1":"할","2":"이","3":"도"},pool:["할","이","도","하","을","는","에","가"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"어디로 갈까 말까 하다가 결국 집에 있었어요.\n결국 + -다가 combine here.\nWhat happened?\n(Was debating where to go, ended up staying home.)",opts:["Debated, then gave up and stayed home","Went out successfully","Decided quickly","Asked someone for help"],ans:"Debated, then gave up and stayed home",hint:"까 말까 = indecision. 결국 = in the end."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l7",title:"고 말다 / 려다가",icon:"💥",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Ended Up / Was About To But...",desc:"-고 말다 / -(으)려다가\n→ When things don't go as planned.\n\n고 말다: ended up doing (unintended)\n려다가: was about to, but then...",goals:["Use -고 말다 for unintended results","Use -(으)려다가 for interrupted intentions","Express frustration about plans gone wrong"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-고 말다",src:"ended up doing (unintended result)",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"go mal-da",note:"Something happened DESPITE trying not to.\n결국 + V-고 말다 is very common.\n\n결국 포기하고 말았어요.\n(Ended up giving up in the end.)\n\nImplies frustration or resignation.\nThe result was NOT what the speaker wanted.",example:"A: 어제 영화 봤어요? B: 네, 안 울려고 했는데 결국 울고 말았어요. A: 그렇게 슬픈 영화였어요? B: 네, 마지막 장면에서 참을 수 없었어요. A: 옆에 앉은 사람도 울었어요? B: 네, 극장 전체가 울고 말았어요. A: 그 정도면 정말 감동적인 영화였네요. B: 맞아요. 보고 나서 한참 동안 멍했어요. A: 저도 그 영화 보고 울었어요. B: 다음에는 코미디를 보자고요.",exampleSrc:"A: Did you watch the movie yesterday? B: Yes, I tried not to cry but ended up crying in the end. A: Was it that sad of a movie? B: Yes, I couldn't hold back at the last scene. A: Did the person sitting next to you also cry? B: Yes, the whole theater ended up crying. A: If it was that much, it must have been a really moving movie. B: Right. I was in a daze for a while after watching it. A: I also cried watching that movie. B: Let's watch a comedy next time.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)려다가",src:"was about to but then...",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"ryeo-da-ga",note:"An intention that was INTERRUPTED.\n려 (intention) + 다가 (but then)\n\n가려다가 안 갔어요.\n(Was about to go but didn't.)\n\n말하려다가 참았어요.\n(Was about to speak but held back.)",example:"A: 어제 민수한테 전화했어요? B: 전화하려다가 그만뒀어요. A: 왜요? 무슨 일이에요? B: 너무 늦은 시간이라서요. 깨울까 봐 걱정했어요. A: 그러면 문자를 보내지 그랬어요. B: 맞아요. 문자를 보내려다가 그것도 잊어버렸어요. A: 오늘은 꼭 연락하세요. B: 네, 점심 때 전화하려다가 회의 때문에 못 했어요. A: 그러면 지금 바로 하세요. B: 알겠어요. 더 이상 미루면 안 되겠어요.",exampleSrc:"A: Did you call Minsu yesterday? B: I was about to call but stopped. A: Why? What happened? B: It was too late at night. I was worried I might wake him up. A: Then you should have sent a text. B: Right. I was about to text but forgot that too. A: Make sure to contact him today. B: Yes, I was about to call at lunch but couldn't because of a meeting. A: Then do it right now. B: Okay. I shouldn't put it off any longer.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"tip",title:"-고 말다 vs -려다가",deepDive:"Combining with other regret patterns:\n\n고 말다 + 할걸:\n 울고 말았어요. 참을걸.\n (Ended up crying. Should've held it in.)\n\n려다가 + 할걸:\n 사려다가 안 샀어요. 살걸.\n (Was about to buy but didn't. Should've bought it.)\n\n고 말다 + 뻔하다:\n 울고 말 뻔했어요.\n (Almost ended up crying.)\n\nThese combinations create rich regret narratives\nthat Korean speakers use naturally in storytelling.",text:"고 말다: the result happened (unwanted)\n 비밀을 말하고 말았어요.\n (I ended up telling the secret.)\n → DID happen, regretfully.\n\n려다가: the result DIDN'T happen\n 말하려다가 참았어요.\n (Was about to tell but held back.)\n → DIDN'T happen, intention interrupted.\n\nOne is 'unfortunately did.'\nOther is 'was going to but didn't.'"},
        {type:"mc",q:"결국 울고 말았어요.\nWhat happened?",opts:["Ended up crying despite trying not to","Stopped crying","Almost cried but didn't","Wanted to cry"],ans:"Ended up crying despite trying not to",hint:"-고 말다 = ended up doing (unintended, unwanted)."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["려","고","어서","으면"],hint:"Intention marker before 다가.",s:"전화하{1}다가 그만뒀어요.\n(Was about to call but stopped.)",a:"려"},
        {type:"mc",q:"비밀을 말하고 말았어요.\n말하려다가 참았어요.\nWhat's the difference?",opts:["First: told the secret (regret). Second: held back (didn't tell).","Both told the secret","Both held back","First held back, second told"],ans:"First: told the secret (regret). Second: held back (didn't tell).",hint:"-고 말다 = did it. -려다가 = was about to but didn't."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Unintended result connector. Regret.",s:"결국 포기하{1} 말았어요. 포기 안 {2}걸.\n(Ended up giving up. Shouldn't have given up.)",blanks:{"1":"고","2":"할"},pool:["고","할","려","할까"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"사려다가 안 샀어요. 살걸.\nTwo patterns:",opts:["-려다가 (interrupted intent) + -(으)ㄹ걸 (should have)","Only -려다가","Only -(으)ㄹ걸","-고 말다 + -(으)ㄹ걸"],ans:"-려다가 (interrupted intent) + -(으)ㄹ걸 (should have)",hint:"Was about to buy but didn't + should have bought."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Intention. Negative outcome worry.",s:"도전하{1}다가 {2}할까 봐 포기했어요.\n(Was about to try but gave up worried about failing.)",blanks:{"1":"려","2":"실패"},pool:["려","실패","고","성공","어서","후회"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Error. Caution. Error again. Caution again.",s:"결국 {1}하고 말았어요. {2}했더라면 {3}하지 않았을 텐데. {4}할걸.\n(Ended up making a mistake. If I had been careful, I wouldn't have made a mistake. Should have been careful.)",blanks:{"1":"실수","2":"조심","3":"실수","4":"조심"},pool:["실수","조심","실수","조심","후회","준비","후회","준비"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"말하려다가 참았는데 결국 말하고 말았어요.\nThe sequence:",opts:["Held back initially, but ended up telling anyway","Told immediately","Never told","Held back successfully"],ans:"Held back initially, but ended up telling anyway",hint:"-려다가 참다 (held back) + -고 말다 (ended up doing)."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Apply. Intention. Plan. Connector. After-turn-back.",s:"{1}하{2}다가 {3}를 바꿨{4} 결국 {5}하고 말았어요.\n(Was about to apply but changed plans. Ended up regretting in the end.)",blanks:{"1":"지원","2":"려","3":"계획","4":"는데","5":"후회"},pool:["지원","려","계획","는데","후회","합격","고","일정","지만","실수"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"결국 울고 말았어요.\n결국 means?\n(In the end, I ended up crying.)",opts:["결국 = in the end / eventually ","결국 = suddenly","결국 = fortunately","결국 = almost"],ans:"결국 = in the end / eventually ",hint:"outcome/conclusion adverb."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Was-about-to stem. Ended-up past. Object.",s:"참{1}려다가 결국 웃고 말{2}어요. 비밀{3} 지키려다가 말해 버렸어요.\n(Tried to hold it in but ended up laughing. Tried to keep the secret but blurted it out.)",blanks:{"1":"으","2":"았","3":"을"},pool:["으","았","을","어","는","이","를","가"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-고 말다 implies the speaker is?\n결국 실수하고 말았어요.\n(In the end, I ended up making a mistake.)",opts:["Frustrated or disappointed by the outcome","Happy about the result","Neutral about it","Surprised but pleased"],ans:"Frustrated or disappointed by the outcome",hint:"-고 말다 carries negative/resigned feelings."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Was-about-to. Subject. Ended-up.",s:"운동하{1}다가 비{2} 와서 집에 갔어요. 결국 포기하{3} 말았어요.\n(Was about to exercise but it rained so went home. In the end, gave up.)",blanks:{"1":"려","2":"가","3":"고"},pool:["려","가","고","는","를","어","이","다"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"고 말다=ended up. 려다가=was going to but...",s:"-고 말다: {1} result, speaker feels {2}.\n-(으)려다가: intention was {3}, but {4} happened.\n(Two patterns about plans going wrong.)",blanks:{"1":"unintended","2":"frustrated","3":"interrupted","4":"something else"},pool:["unintended","frustrated","interrupted","something else","planned","happy","completed","nothing"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Was-about-to. Object. Ended-up past. Subject.",s:"다이어트하{1}다가 치킨{2} 먹고 말{3}어요. 의지{4} 약했어요.\n(Was trying to diet but ended up eating chicken. My willpower was weak.)",blanks:{"1":"려","2":"을","3":"았","4":"가"},pool:["려","을","았","가","는","를","어","이"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Was-about-to. Ended-up past. Subject.",s:"공부하{1}다가 게임하고 말{2}어요. 의지{3} 약해요.\n(Was about to study but ended up gaming. My willpower is weak.)",blanks:{"1":"려","2":"았","3":"가"},pool:["려","았","가","는","어","이","을","에"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"사려다가 안 샀어요 vs 사고 말았어요.\nKey difference?\n(Was going to buy but didn't vs ended up buying.)",opts:["려다가: didn't do it; 고 말다: did it (reluctantly)","Same meaning","려다가: did it; 고 말다: didn't","Both mean didn't do it"],ans:"려다가: didn't do it; 고 말다: did it (reluctantly)",hint:"려다가=intention interrupted. 고 말다=it happened despite wishes."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l8",title:"참이다",icon:"⏰",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Was Just About To",desc:"-(으)려던 참이다\n→ 'I was just about to do that!'\n\nA timely coincidence expression.\nSomeone suggests exactly what you were planning.",goals:["Use -(으)려던 참이다 for timely coincidence","Distinguish from -(으)려다가 (interrupted)","Review all intention/regret patterns together"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"-(으)려던 참이다",src:"was just about to (timely coincidence)",pos:"part",gender:null,phonetic:"ryeo-deon cham-i-da",note:"Coincidence: you were planning to do\nexactly what someone just suggested.\n\n참 = moment/occasion\n마침 = just then / coincidentally\n\n마침 가려던 참이었어요.\n(I was just about to go.)",example:"A: 점심 먹으러 갈래요? B: 마침 저도 먹으러 가려던 참이었어요! A: 정말요? 어디로 갈까요? B: 새로 생긴 식당이 있는데 가 볼까요? A: 좋아요. 마침 거기 가 보고 싶었어요. B: 그러면 빨리 나가요. 점심시간에 사람이 많거든요. A: 혹시 예약해야 하나요? B: 아니요, 마침 전화하려던 참이었는데 줄이 안 긴다고 해요. A: 완벽하네요. 오늘 운이 좋은 것 같아요. B: 맞아요. 마침 날씨도 좋으니까 걸어가요.",exampleSrc:"A: Want to go eat lunch? B: I was just about to go eat too! A: Really? Where shall we go? B: There's a new restaurant. Shall we try it? A: Sure. I just happened to want to try that place. B: Then let's hurry. It gets crowded during lunch. A: Do we need a reservation? B: No, I was just about to call, but they said there's no long line. A: Perfect. I think we're lucky today. B: Right. The weather is nice too, so let's walk.",funFact:"Korean particles attach to nouns to show their role in the sentence. The particle, not word order, determines meaning."},
        {type:"tip",title:"참이다 vs 려다가",deepDive:"Review of intention patterns:\n\n-(으)려고: basic purpose\n 공부하려고 도서관에 갔어요.\n (Went to library to study.)\n\n-고자: formal purpose (U21)\n 발전하고자 노력합니다.\n (I strive to develop.)\n\n-(으)려다가: interrupted intention\n 가려다가 안 갔어요.\n (Was about to go but didn't.)\n\n-(으)려던 참이다: timely coincidence\n 마침 가려던 참이었어요!\n (Was just about to go!)",text:"Both involve intentions, different outcomes:\n\n려던 참이다: intention + timely match\n A: 밥 먹으러 갈래요?\n B: 마침 먹으려던 참이었어요!\n (I was just about to eat!)\n → Happy coincidence!\n\n려다가: intention + interruption\n 먹으려다가 전화가 왔어요.\n (Was about to eat but got a call.)\n → Interrupted, didn't happen.\n\n참이다 = positive (great timing!)\n려다가 = neutral/negative (plans changed)"},
        {type:"mc",q:"마침 전화하려던 참이었어요.\nThe speaker:",opts:["Was just about to call (coincidence)","Already called","Doesn't want to call","Was interrupted while calling"],ans:"Was just about to call (coincidence)",hint:"마침 signals a coincidence. What was the speaker in the middle of getting ready to do?"},
        {type:"fb",opts:["먹","먹은","먹는","먹을"],hint:"Verb stem before 으려던 참.",s:"마침 {1}으려던 참이었어요!\n(I was just about to eat!)",a:"먹"},
        {type:"mc",q:"A: 커피 마실래요?\nB: 마침 마시려던 참이었어요!\nWhat is the mood?",opts:["Happy coincidence (great timing!)","Disappointment","Indecision","Worry"],ans:"Happy coincidence (great timing!)",hint:"참이다 = positive timing match."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Physical activity. Connector (and so).",s:"마침 {1}하려던 참이었{2} 같이 가요!\n(I was just about to exercise! Let's go together!)",blanks:{"1":"운동","2":"는데"},pool:["운동","는데","공부","지만","식사","어서"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"가려다가 안 갔어요.\n가려던 참이었어요.\nWhat's the difference?",opts:["First: was going to but didn't. Second: was just about to (coincidence).","Both mean the same","First is positive, second is negative","Both are about regret"],ans:"First: was going to but didn't. Second: was just about to (coincidence).",hint:"-려다가 = interrupted. -려던 참 = timely coincidence."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Study. Same activity together.",s:"{1}하려던 참인데 같이 {2}할까요?\n(Was just about to study, shall we study together?)",blanks:{"1":"공부","2":"공부"},pool:["공부","공부","운동","운동","식사","식사"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Contact. Sentence end. Contact again. Intention marker.",s:"마침 {1}하려던 참이었{2} 아까 {3}하{4}다가 전화가 와서 못 했거든요.\n(Was just about to do it. Earlier I was about to call but a phone call came so I couldn't.)",blanks:{"1":"연락","2":"어요.","3":"연락","4":"려"},pool:["연락","어요.","연락","려","공부","는데.","전화","고"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"U24 intention patterns ranked by outcome:\nA: -려고 (basic purpose)\nB: -려다가 (interrupted)\nC: -려던 참이다 (coincidence)\nD: -고 말다 (unintended result)",opts:["A: planned. B: didn't happen. C: about to happen. D: happened unwantedly.","All the same","A = B = C = D","Only D has a result"],ans:"A: planned. B: didn't happen. C: about to happen. D: happened unwantedly.",hint:"Each intention pattern has a different outcome."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Failure worry. Quit. Intention. Challenge. Advance work.",s:"{1}할까 봐 {2}하{3}다가 결국 {4}하고 말았어요. {5}할걸.\n(Worried about failing, was about to give up, but ended up trying. Should have prepared.)",blanks:{"1":"실패","2":"포기","3":"려","4":"도전","5":"준비"},pool:["실패","포기","려","도전","준비","합격","지원","고","실수","공부"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Apply. End. Preparation.",s:"마침 {1}하려던 참이었{2} {3}했더라면 더 좋았을 텐데.\n(Was just about to apply. If I had prepared, it would've been better.)",blanks:{"1":"지원","2":"어요.","3":"준비"},pool:["지원","어요.","준비","합격","는데.","공부"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"마침 전화하려던 참이었어요!\n마침 means?\n(I was just about to call, what timing!)",opts:["마침 = just then / by coincidence (timing word)","마침 = finally","마침 = unfortunately","마침 = always"],ans:"마침 = just then / by coincidence (timing word)",hint:"Happy coincidence marker."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"About-to stem. Past (was). suggestion.",s:"밥 먹{1}려던 참이{2}어요. 같이 먹{3}래요?\n(I was just about to eat. Want to eat together?)",blanks:{"1":"으","2":"었","3":"을"},pool:["으","었","을","는","이","어","는","가"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"-(으)려던 참이다 vs -(으)려다가:\n참 = timing match (positive).\n다가 = interruption (often negative).\nKey difference?\n(Two intention patterns.)",opts:["참이다: happy coincidence; 려다가: plan got interrupted","Same meaning","참이다 = negative; 려다가 = positive","Both are about interruptions"],ans:"참이다: happy coincidence; 려다가: plan got interrupted",hint:"참 = perfect timing. 다가 = but then..."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"About-to stem. Subject. Past.",s:"마침 나가{1}려던 참에 택배{2} 왔어요. 딱 맞{3}어요!\n(Just as I was about to leave, a delivery came. Perfect timing!)",blanks:{"1":"으","2":"가","3":"았"},pool:["으","가","았","는","를","어","이","에"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"려고=plain. 려다가=but. 참이다=coincidence. 고자=written.",s:"-(으)려고: {1} intention.\n-(으)려다가: intention {2}.\n-(으)려던 참이다: intention + {3} timing.\n-고자: {4} intention.\n(Four intention patterns compared.)",blanks:{"1":"simple","2":"interrupted","3":"perfect","4":"formal"},pool:["simple","interrupted","perfect","formal","strong","completed","bad","casual"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"About-to stem. Subject. Object. Polite.",s:"커피 사{1}려던 참에 친구{2} 커피{3} 사 줬어요. 고마워{4}!\n(Just about to buy coffee when my friend bought me one. Thanks!)",blanks:{"1":"으","2":"가","3":"를","4":"요"},pool:["으","가","를","요","는","이","을","서"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"마침 퇴근하려던 참이었어요.\n퇴근하다 means?\n(I was just about to leave work.)",opts:["퇴근하다 = to leave work / clock out ","퇴근하다 = to arrive at work","퇴근하다 = to skip work","퇴근하다 = to overtime"],ans:"퇴근하다 = to leave work / clock out ",hint:"workplace vocabulary."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"About-to stem. Subject. Honorific past.",s:"질문하{1}려던 참에 선생님{2} 먼저 설명해 주셨{3}요.\n(Just about to ask when the teacher explained first.)",blanks:{"1":"으","2":"이","3":"어"},pool:["으","이","어","는","을","가","는","아"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Four intention patterns in order of learning level:\n-(으)려고 → -고자 → -(으)려다가 → -(으)려던 참이다 .\nWhat does -(으)려고 express?\n(Tracking the progression.)",opts:["basic intention pattern","basic particle","intermediate grammar","advanced pattern"],ans:"basic intention pattern",hint:"One of the earliest intention patterns taught."}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l9",title:"한의 문화",icon:"🎭",xp:20,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"The Korean Soul of Regret",desc:"한의 문화\n→ Understanding 한, 아쉬움, and Korean emotional expression.\n\nKorean culture has deep concepts of regret, longing,\nand bittersweet acceptance that shape the language.",goals:["Understand 한 as a cultural concept","Connect grammar patterns to Korean emotional expression","Use regret vocabulary in cultural contexts"]},
        {type:"tip",title:"한 (恨) in Korean Life",deepDive:"Historical roots of 한:\n\nKorea's history includes invasion, colonization,\nwar, and division. This collective experience\ncreated a shared emotional vocabulary.\n\n한 is both personal and collective:\n- 이산가족의 한 (families separated by war)\n- 못 다 한 꿈 (unfulfilled dreams)\n- 세월의 한 (regrets of passing time)\n\n한 is not self-pity. It's dignified sorrow\nmixed with resilience. Koreans say:\n'한이 있어야 예술이 된다.'\n(You need 한 to create art.)",text:"한 is NOT just 'regret' or 'resentment.'\nIt's a complex emotion unique to Korean culture:\n\n한이 맺히다 = 한 builds up (unresolved)\n한을 풀다 = release/resolve 한\n한이 서리다 = 한 accumulates (poetic)\n\nAppears in:\n- 판소리 (traditional singing): raw emotion\n- 드라마: characters carry 한\n- 일상: '한이 맺혀요' (I carry unresolved 한)"},
        {type:"teach",trg:"한",src:"deep unresolved longing / resentment",pos:"noun",gender:null,phonetic:"han",note:"One of the most important Korean cultural concepts.\n한(恨) = deep accumulated sorrow\n\n한이 맺히다 = 한 builds up\n한을 풀다 = to resolve 한\n한이 서리다 = 한 lingers (poetic)",example:"A: 할머니가 왜 그렇게 슬퍼 보이세요? B: 할머니는 한이 맺혀 있어요. 고향에 못 돌아가셨거든요. A: 어디가 고향이세요? B: 북한이에요. 전쟁 때 남쪽으로 오셨어요. A: 가족을 못 만나셨겠네요. B: 네, 그 한을 평생 안고 사셨어요. A: 한을 풀 수 있는 방법이 없을까요? B: 이산가족 상봉이 있지만 기회가 적어요. A: 정말 가슴 아픈 이야기네요. B: 한국 역사를 이해하면 한이라는 감정을 더 잘 알 수 있어요.",exampleSrc:"A: Why does grandmother look so sad? B: Grandmother carries deep unresolved grief. She couldn't return to her hometown. A: Where is her hometown? B: North Korea. She came south during the war. A: She must not have been able to see her family. B: Yes, she lived her whole life carrying that grief. A: Isn't there a way to resolve the grief? B: There are separated family reunions, but opportunities are few. A: That's really a heartbreaking story. B: If you understand Korean history, you can better understand the emotion called han.",funFact:"Built from Chinese characters (Hanja). About 60% of Korean vocabulary has Hanja roots."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"이산가족",src:"separated families (from Korean War)",pos:"noun",gender:null,phonetic:"i-san-ga-jok",note:"COMPOUND: 이(separate/離) + 산(scatter/散) +\n가(family/家) + 족(clan/族).\nScattered families from the Korean War.\nRegular reunions are held at 금강산.",example:"이산가족의 한은 깊습니다.\n(The 한 of separated families is deep.)",exampleSrc:"The 한 of separated families is deep.",funFact:"Korean builds words by combining meaning blocks. Understanding the parts unlocks entire word families."},
        {type:"mc",q:"한이 맺히다 means:",opts:["Unresolved 한 accumulates in someone","한 is released","한 disappears","한 is shared"],ans:"Unresolved 한 accumulates in someone",hint:"맺히다 = to form/build up. 한 that hasn't been resolved."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Scattered. Deep emotion. Period. Know-as.",s:"{1}가족의 {2}은 깊습니{3} {4}다시피 아직도 만나지 못하는 가족이 많습니다.\n(The 한 of separated families is deep. As you know, there are still many families who can't meet.)",blanks:{"1":"이산","2":"한","3":"다.","4":"아시"},pool:["이산","한","다.","아시","전쟁","후회","요.","보시"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"한이 있어야 예술이 된다.\nThis Korean saying means:",opts:["You need deep sorrow to create great art","Art removes all sadness","Happy people make better art","한 and art are unrelated"],ans:"You need deep sorrow to create great art",hint:"한 fuels artistic expression in Korean culture."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Go (back). Deep cultural emotion.",s:"할머니가 고향에 못 돌아{1}셔서 {2}이 맺혀 있어요.\n(Grandmother can't return to her hometown, so she carries deep 한.)",blanks:{"1":"가","2":"한"},pool:["가","한","와","후회","다녀","아쉬움"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Past return. Deep emotion. Regret form.",s:"고향에 돌아{1}더라면 {2}을 풀 수 있었을 텐데. 돌아{3}걸.\n(If I could have returned home, I could have resolved the 한. Should have gone back.)",blanks:{"1":"갔","2":"한","3":"갈"},pool:["갔","한","갈","왔","후회","올"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"보도에 따르면 이산가족 상봉이 줄고 있는 것으로 나타났습니다.\nHow many U23 patterns?",opts:["Two: 에 따르면 (citation) + 것으로 나타났다 (found)","One: 에 따르면","Three: 에 따르면 + 나타났다 + 보도","Zero"],ans:"Two: 에 따르면 (citation) + 것으로 나타났다 (found)",hint:"News citation + news result cliche."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Deep emotion. Cause (formal). Written 'and'. Same emotion resolved.",s:"한국인의 {1}은 역사{2} 인해 깊어졌{3} 예술로 {4}을 풀기도 합니다.\n(Korean 한 deepened due to history, and they also resolve 한 through art.)",blanks:{"1":"한","2":"으로","3":"으며","4":"한"},pool:["한","으로","으며","한","후회","에","고","아쉬움"]},
        {type:"match",pairs:[{trg:"한이 맺히다",src:"한 builds up"},{trg:"한을 풀다",src:"resolve 한"},{trg:"이산가족",src:"separated families"},{trg:"아쉬움",src:"bittersweet regret"}]},
        {type:"mc",q:"한이 맺히다: 한 builds up inside.\n안 (inside) appears in many emotion expressions.\nWhat does 맺히다 literally mean?\n(Cultural expression about accumulated grief.)",opts:["맺히다 = to form/accumulate (like a knot)","맺히다 = to disappear","맺히다 = to enjoy","맺히다 = to forget"],ans:"맺히다 = to form/accumulate (like a knot)",hint:"A knot of emotion forming inside."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"To-person. Subject. Negation. Object + resolve.",s:"이산가족{1} 한{2} 맺혔어요. 만나{3} 못 해 한{4} 풀 수 없었어요.\n(Separated families accumulated grief. Unable to meet, couldn't resolve their grief.)",blanks:{"1":"에게","2":"이","3":"지","4":"을"},pool:["에게","이","지","을","에","를","의","는"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"한을 풀다: to resolve or release 한.\n풀다 also means?\n(Resolving deep grief.)",opts:["풀다 = to untie/solve/release ","풀다 = to tighten","풀다 = to create","풀다 = to increase"],ans:"풀다 = to untie/solve/release ",hint:"verb: untie a knot, solve a problem, release tension."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object (family). Subject (grief). Would-have.",s:"가족{1} 만났더라면 한{2} 풀렸{3} 텐데.\n(If they had met their family, the grief would have been resolved.)",blanks:{"1":"을","2":"이","3":"을"},pool:["을","이","을","이","를","가","는","에"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Forms inside. Gets resolved. Born from pain. Divided.",s:"한이 맺히다: grief {1}.\n한을 풀다: grief {2}.\n판소리: traditional art born from {3}.\n이산가족: families {4} by war.\n(Korean cultural vocabulary.)",blanks:{"1":"accumulates","2":"is released","3":"한","4":"separated"},pool:["accumulates","is released","한","separated","disappears","grows","joy","united"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Topic. Subject. Object. Into (transformation).",s:"판소리{1} 한{2} 담긴 예술이에요. 슬픔{3} 아름다움{4} 바꿔요.\n(Pansori is art containing 한. It turns sadness into beauty.)",blanks:{"1":"는","2":"이","3":"을","4":"으로"},pool:["는","이","을","으로","에","가","의","를"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"그때 더 시간을 보냈더라면 한이 안 맺혔을 텐데.\nHow many patterns in this sentence?\n(If I had spent more time then, grief wouldn't have formed.)",opts:["3: -았/었더라면 + 맺히다 (한 vocab) + -(으)ㄹ 텐데","1 pattern","2 patterns","4 patterns"],ans:"3: -았/었더라면 + 맺히다 (한 vocab) + -(으)ㄹ 텐데",hint:"Counterfactual + cultural vocab + would-have."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Plural. Topic. Special (modifier). Subject.",s:"한국 사람{1}에게 한{2} 특별{3} 감정이에요. 모든 사람{4} 이해할 수 있어요.\n(For Korean people, 한 is a special emotion. Everyone can understand.)",blanks:{"1":"들","2":"은","3":"한","4":"이"},pool:["들","은","한","이","의","이","는","을"]}
  ]},
  {id:"kou24l10",title:"종합 평가",icon:"📋",xp:25,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Unit 24 Assessment",desc:"U24 종합 평가\n→ All regret and hypothetical patterns reviewed.\n\n10 patterns: -(으)ㄹ걸, 뻔하다, 텐데, 테니까,\n더라면, 까 봐, 까 말까, 고 말다, 려다가, 려던 참이다",goals:["Demonstrate mastery of all U24 patterns","Choose the correct regret pattern for each context","Combine multiple patterns in complex sentences","Distinguish intention, worry, and regret"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"더 열심히 공부할걸.\n-(으)ㄹ걸 expresses:",opts:["Mild regret about a past choice","A future plan","A current wish","A counterfactual condition"],ans:"Mild regret about a past choice",hint:"Should have studied harder. Past action regret."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["질","진","지는","졌"],hint:"Near-miss potential form.",s:"하마터면 넘어{1} 뻔했어요!\n(I almost fell!)",a:"질"},
        {type:"mc",q:"피곤할 텐데 vs 도와줄 테니까.\nKey difference:",opts:["텐데 = expectation + concern; 테니까 = promise as reason","Both express promises","Both express expectations","텐데 is past, 테니까 is future"],ans:"텐데 = expectation + concern; 테니까 = promise as reason",hint:"텐데 guesses situation. 테니까 gives reason/promise."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Past counterfactual. Would-have result.",s:"공부{1}더라면 합격{2} 텐데.\n(If I had studied, I would have passed.)",blanks:{"1":"했","2":"했을"},pool:["했","했을","하면","할"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"실패할까 봐 vs 갈까 말까.\nDifference:",opts:["까 봐 = worry about bad outcome; 까 말까 = indecision","Both mean worry","Both mean indecision","까 봐 is formal, 까 말까 is casual"],ans:"까 봐 = worry about bad outcome; 까 말까 = indecision",hint:"Worry vs. torn between options."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Unintended result. Regret about not holding back.",s:"결국 울{1} 말았어요. 참{2}걸.\n(Ended up crying. Should have held it in.)",blanks:{"1":"고","2":"을"},pool:["고","을","어서","았"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"마침 가려던 참이었어요!\n-(으)려던 참이다 expresses:",opts:["Timely coincidence (was just about to)","Interrupted intention","Unintended result","Regret"],ans:"Timely coincidence (was just about to)",hint:"참이다 = happy timing match."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Quit. Intention. Challenge.",s:"{1}하{2}다가 결국 {3}하고 말았어요.\n(Was about to give up, but ended up challenging in the end.)",blanks:{"1":"포기","2":"려","3":"도전"},pool:["포기","려","도전","합격","고","실패"]},
        {type:"match",pairs:[{trg:"-(으)ㄹ걸",src:"should have (regret)"},{trg:"-(으)ㄹ 뻔하다",src:"almost did (near-miss)"},{trg:"-았/었더라면",src:"if I had (counterfactual)"},{trg:"-고 말다",src:"ended up (unintended)"}]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Fail worry. Caution. But. Challenge. Succeed. Challenge regret.",s:"{1}할까 봐 {2}했{3} {4}했더라면 {5}했을 텐데. {6}할걸.\n(Worried about failing, I was cautious. If I had tried, I would have succeeded. Should have tried.)",blanks:{"1":"실패","2":"조심","3":"지만","4":"도전","5":"성공","6":"도전"},pool:["실패","조심","지만","도전","성공","도전","합격","준비","는데","포기","합격","포기"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"다음 중 U24에서 배운 패턴이 아닌 것은?",opts:["-(으)로 인해 (due to .  U23)","-(으)ㄹ걸 (should have)","-(으)ㄹ 뻔하다 (almost did)","-고 말다 (ended up doing)"],ans:"-(으)로 인해 (due to .  U23)",hint:"으로 인해 is formal cause from U23 (news). U24 is about regret."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Survey. University. Regret. Hearsay. Past choice.",s:"{1}에 따르면 {2}생의 대부분이 진로를 {3}한다{4} 저도 다른 전공을 {5}더라면 좋았을 텐데.\n(According to a survey, most students regret their career choice. I also wish I had chosen a different major.)",blanks:{"1":"조사","2":"대학","3":"후회","4":"더라.","5":"골랐"},pool:["조사","대학","후회","더라.","골랐","통계","고등학","실수","던데.","공부했"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Apply. Connect. Fail. Quit. Intent. Challenge. End. Prepare. Pass.",s:"마침 {1}하려던 참이었{2} {3}할까 봐 {4}하{5}다가 결국 {6}하고 말았{7} {8}했더라면 {9}했을 텐데.\n(Was just about to apply. Was about to give up worried about failing. Ended up trying. If I had prepared, I would have succeeded.)",blanks:{"1":"지원","2":"는데","3":"실패","4":"포기","5":"려","6":"도전","7":"어요.","8":"준비","9":"합격"},pool:["지원","는데","실패","포기","려","도전","어요.","준비","합격","공부","지만","성공","고","실수","고","운동","습니다.","연습","성공"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"About-to stem. Subject. Conditional.",s:"전화하{1}려던 참에 메시지{2} 왔어요. 안 보냈{3}면 전화할걸!\n(Was just about to call when a message came. If they hadn't sent it, I should have called!)",blanks:{"1":"으","2":"가","3":"으"},pool:["으","가","으","는","를","어","이","는"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Match the emotion to the pattern:\n안도감 (relief) → 뻔했다\n후회 (regret) → 걸\n걱정 (worry) → 까 봐\n좌절 (frustration) → 고 말다\nWhich pairing is INCORRECT?\n(Testing emotion-pattern connections.)",opts:["All four pairings are correct","뻔했다 should be worry","걸 should be relief","까 봐 should be frustration"],ans:"All four pairings are correct",hint:"Relief at near-miss. Regret at own choice. Worry about future. Frustrated at outcome."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Object. Would-have. Modifier (near-miss thing).",s:"일찍 출발했더라면 비행기{1} 탔{2} 텐데. 놓칠 뻔{3} 게 아니라 정말 놓쳤어요.\n(If I had left early, I would have caught the plane. It wasn't almost missing it, I really missed it.)",blanks:{"1":"를","2":"을","3":"한"},pool:["를","을","한","이","는","어","가","을"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Light self-blame. Wish. Full counterfactual. Almost-happened.",s:"Mild: -(으)ㄹ{1}. Medium: -(으)면 {2}. Strong: -았/었{3}.\nNear-miss: -(으)ㄹ {4}.\n(Regret intensity scale.)",blanks:{"1":"걸","2":"좋겠다","3":"더라면","4":"뻔하다"},pool:["걸","좋겠다","더라면","뻔하다","텐데","까 봐","고 말다","참이다"]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"About-to stem. Subject. Conditional.",s:"먹{1}려던 참에 배달{2} 왔어요. 안 시켰{3}면 직접 만들걸!\n(Was just about to eat when delivery came. If I hadn't ordered, I should have made it myself!)",blanks:{"1":"으","2":"이","3":"으"},pool:["으","이","으","는","가","어","을","에"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"ALL U24 patterns use -(으)ㄹ modifier EXCEPT?\n걸, 뻔하다, 텐데, 테니까, 까 봐, 까 말까...\nWhich pattern uses -았/었 instead?\n(Checking the tense markers.)",opts:["-았/었더라면 uses PAST tense, not future -(으)ㄹ","All use -(으)ㄹ","고 말다 uses past","려던 참이다 uses past"],ans:"-았/었더라면 uses PAST tense, not future -(으)ㄹ",hint:"더라면 is the only pattern starting with past tense marker."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Ended-up. Future (worry). Hearsay/background.",s:"결국 포기하{1} 말았어요. 포기하{2}까 봐 걱정했{3}데 정말 포기했어요.\n(Ended up giving up. Was worried about giving up, and really did.)",blanks:{"1":"고","2":"ㄹ","3":"는"},pool:["고","ㄹ","는","어","을","은","다","에"]}
  ]}
]};
